      "writtenOn": "2026-05-05T10:15:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Restructured along the lines you suggested: lifted `d` out of the for clause, dropped the inline `haveCUEMod`, and added `parent \u003d\u003d mdir` to the break condition so the upward step stops on hitting the module root. I kept the `d !\u003d mdir` for-condition rather than going to `for { ... }`, because `loc.Dir` can equal `mloc.Dir` on entry (the `pkgPath \u003d\u003d mpath` branch above sets `loc \u003d mloc`), and we mustn\u0027t stat the module\u0027s own cue.mod/module.cue in that case. Happy to switch to the bare `for { }` if you\u0027d prefer adding an explicit guard for that case instead.",
